const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the Sony WH-1000XM5 worth it over the XM4?', a: 'Yes, if you value better call quality, improved comfort, and the strongest ANC on the market. The XM5 has eight microphones and a new V1 processor that edges out the XM4 in noise cancellation and voice pickup. If you already own the XM4 and do not take many calls, the upgrade is marginal — the XM4 still folds and has nearly identical battery life.' },
  { q: 'How long does the WH-1000XM5 battery last?', a: 'Sony rates the battery at 30 hours with ANC on and 40 hours with ANC off. In our testing, with ANC on and mixed LDAC and SBC streaming, we averaged 28 to 30 hours per charge. A three-minute quick charge gives about three hours of playback, and a full charge from empty takes about 1.5 hours over USB-C.' },
  { q: 'Does the WH-1000XM5 support multipoint Bluetooth?', a: 'Yes. The XM5 pairs with two devices simultaneously over Bluetooth 5.2. We tested it with a Mac and a phone paired at the same time — music from the Mac paused automatically when a call came in on the phone, and resumed when the call ended. Multipoint works reliably once both devices are paired, though the initial setup requires re-pairing the second device if you switch devices often.' },
